               <p>JOHN DAY. On the 20th of September the prisoner lodged at my house. About six o'clock in the morning his fellow-lodger called me up; I opened a room to get something, and left it open. In about half an hour I missed two tea-spoons, and found the prisoner was gone. About four o'clock the constable took him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18190915-272-person2294">
                  HENRY 
                  HOWARD
               <interp inst="t18190915-272-person2294" type="surname" value="HOWARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190915-272-person2294" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190915-272-person2294" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. I apprehended the prisoner, and found four tea-spoons in his pocket. He said he found them - he afterwards said they were Day's.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner. I am an orphan. I was driven to it by distress.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18190915-272-verdict1470" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18190915-272-verdict1470" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 15.</p>
